From Programming Basics to Browser Interactivity
A versatile language for the web and beyond
- Runs in browsers and on servers (Node.js)
- Used to build interactive web applications
- Can be used for frontend, backend, and even mobile apps
- Execute commands and return a value
Working with different kinds of data
- Primitive types: string, number, boolean, null, undefined, symbol
A class allows us to define a custom kind of "variable type".
Actually a class creates a new object type (like a blueprint) and
defines a constructor function to create instances of that type.
Connecting code to the web page
- Can access and manipulate HTML via the DOM
- Place JS in <script> tags or link external files
JavaScript’s way to interact with the page
- Every HTML element becomes a JS object
- Respond to user actions like clicks, input, etc.
- Connect to a backend or external API
- Node.js runs JavaScript outside the browser
- Great for backend services and CLI tools
- Uses modules, file system access, HTTP servers
- Use let, const, and (less commonly) var
- const for values that don't change
- let for values that may change
